PRINCIPLE OF LEAST KNOWLEDGE(RULES)
->Take an object,now from any method, in that object , principle that tells you to invoke only methods tha belong to
1.The object itself;
2. THe object passed in a parameter to the method;
3. Any object that the method creates.
4.Any object with (has a) relationship;


STANDARD DEFINITION OF FACADE PATTERN
Facade design provides a simplified, unified interface to a set of complex subsytems. It hides the complexity of the System
and expose only what is neccessary


